Great question! Here's the right approach — the key insight is to **extract design tokens programmatically using browser DevTools**, not by eyeballing or asking AI to guess.

Here's the complete strategy:

**The approach: run a script in DevTools Console**

You paste a JavaScript snippet into the browser console while on the target website. It crawls the DOM and computes styles programmatically — extracting exact colors, fonts, spacing, border radii, shadows, etc. This gives you a machine-accurate JSON, not an approximation.Here's the complete script you paste into **DevTools → Console**:

```javascript
(function extractDesignTokens() {
  const all = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('*'));
  const freq = (arr) => {
    const map = {};
    arr.forEach(v => { if (v) map[v] = (map[v] || 0) + 1; });
    return Object.entries(map).sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]).slice(0, 20).map(e => e[0]);
  };

  // --- Colors ---
  const bgColors = [], textColors = [], borderColors = [];
  all.forEach(el => {
    const s = getComputedStyle(el);
    bgColors.push(s.backgroundColor);
    textColors.push(s.color);
    borderColors.push(s.borderTopColor);
  });

  // --- Typography ---
  const fontFamilies = [], fontSizes = [], fontWeights = [], lineHeights = [];
  all.forEach(el => {
    const s = getComputedStyle(el);
    fontFamilies.push(s.fontFamily);
    fontSizes.push(s.fontSize);
    fontWeights.push(s.fontWeight);
    lineHeights.push(s.lineHeight);
  });

  // --- Spacing (padding/margin) ---
  const spacingValues = [];
  all.forEach(el => {
    const s = getComputedStyle(el);
    ['paddingTop','paddingRight','paddingBottom','paddingLeft',
     'marginTop','marginRight','marginBottom','marginLeft'].forEach(p => {
      const v = parseFloat(s[p]);
      if (v > 0) spacingValues.push(Math.round(v));
    });
  });
  const spacingScale = [...new Set(spacingValues.sort((a, b) => a - b))].slice(0, 16);

  // --- Border Radius ---
  const radii = [];
  all.forEach(el => {
    const v = getComputedStyle(el).borderTopLeftRadius;
    if (v && v !== '0px') radii.push(v);
  });

  // --- Shadows ---
  const shadows = [];
  all.forEach(el => {
    const v = getComputedStyle(el).boxShadow;
    if (v && v !== 'none') shadows.push(v);
  });

  // --- CSS Variables (design tokens if using a design system) ---
  const cssVars = {};
  const rootStyles = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
  for (const prop of rootStyles) {
    if (prop.startsWith('--')) {
      cssVars[prop] = rootStyles.getPropertyValue(prop).trim();
    }
  }

  // --- Layout ---
  const body = document.body;
  const bodyStyle = getComputedStyle(body);
  const layout = {
    maxWidth: bodyStyle.maxWidth,
    containerWidth: document.documentElement.clientWidth + 'px',
    bodyPadding: bodyStyle.padding,
  };

  // --- Component-level scan (buttons, inputs, headings) ---
  const componentTokens = {};
  const componentSelectors = {
    h1: 'h1', h2: 'h2', h3: 'h3', h4: 'h4',
    paragraph: 'p',
    button: 'button, [role="button"], .btn',
    input: 'input[type="text"], input[type="email"], textarea',
    link: 'a',
    card: '[class*="card"], [class*="Card"]',
    nav: 'nav, header',
  };
  for (const [name, selector] of Object.entries(componentSelectors)) {
    const el = document.querySelector(selector);
    if (el) {
      const s = getComputedStyle(el);
      componentTokens[name] = {
        fontSize: s.fontSize,
        fontWeight: s.fontWeight,
        fontFamily: s.fontFamily,
        color: s.color,
        backgroundColor: s.backgroundColor,
        padding: `${s.paddingTop} ${s.paddingRight} ${s.paddingBottom} ${s.paddingLeft}`,
        borderRadius: s.borderTopLeftRadius,
        border: s.border,
        lineHeight: s.lineHeight,
        letterSpacing: s.letterSpacing,
      };
    }
  }

  // --- Image assets (logo, icons) ---
  const images = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('img')).slice(0, 10).map(img => ({
    src: img.src,
    alt: img.alt,
    width: img.naturalWidth,
    height: img.naturalHeight,
  }));

  // --- Assemble final JSON ---
  const tokens = {
    meta: {
      url: location.href,
      title: document.title,
      extractedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
    },
    cssVariables: cssVars,
    colors: {
      backgrounds: freq(bgColors).filter(c => c !== 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)'),
      text: freq(textColors),
      borders: freq(borderColors).filter(c => c !== 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)'),
    },
    typography: {
      fontFamilies: freq(fontFamilies),
      fontSizes: [...new Set(freq(fontSizes))].sort((a, b) => parseFloat(a) - parseFloat(b)),
      fontWeights: [...new Set(freq(fontWeights))],
      lineHeights: freq(lineHeights).slice(0, 8),
    },
    spacing: spacingScale,
    borderRadius: freq(radii).slice(0, 8),
    shadows: [...new Set(shadows)].slice(0, 6),
    layout,
    components: componentTokens,
    images,
  };

  console.log('=== DESIGN TOKENS JSON ===');
  console.log(JSON.stringify(tokens, null, 2));
  copy(JSON.stringify(tokens, null, 2)); // auto-copies to clipboard
  return tokens;
})();
```

**How to use it:**

1. Open the target website in Chrome/Edge/Firefox
2. Press `F12` → go to the **Console** tab
3. Paste the entire script and hit Enter
4. The JSON is printed AND auto-copied to your clipboard (`copy()` works in Chrome)
5. Save it as `design-tokens.json`

**What you get in the JSON:**

- `cssVariables` — any `--custom-properties` (goldmine if they use a design system like Tailwind, MUI, or custom tokens)
- `colors.backgrounds/text/borders` — top 20 most-used actual computed colors across all elements
- `typography` — font families, all sizes in use, weights, line heights
- `spacing` — deduplicated spacing scale derived from real padding/margin values
- `borderRadius` — all corner radius values actually used
- `shadows` — exact `box-shadow` values
- `components` — per-component styles for h1–h4, p, button, input, a, card, nav
- `images` — logo and image assets with dimensions

**Then give the AI this prompt with your JSON:**

> "Here is a design token JSON extracted programmatically from the site I want to replicate. Build the UI using these exact values — use the `cssVariables` as your design system foundation, `components` for element-level styles, and `colors`/`typography`/`spacing` for the overall system. Do not invent values."

This gives the AI precise, grounded values instead of guessing — which is where most AI-generated UI clones fall apart.
